#. Tag: title
#: adm_shell.xml:891
#, no-c-format
msgid "Working with Common Flow Constructs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_shell.xml:893
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To control the flow of your script, a shell has <command>while</command>, "
"<command>if</command>, <command>for</command> and <command>case</command> "
"constructs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: adm_shell.xml:902
#, no-c-format
msgid "The if Control Command"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_shell.xml:903
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>if</command> command is used to check expressions. For example, "
"the following code tests whether the current user is Tux:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: adm_shell.xml:907
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"if test $USER = \"tux\"; then\n"
"  echo \"Hello Tux.\"\n"
"else\n"
"  echo \"You are not Tux.\"\n"
"fi"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_shell.xml:908
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The test expression can be as complex or simple as possible. The following "
"expression checks if the file <filename>foo.txt</filename> exists:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: adm_shell.xml:912
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"if test -e /tmp/foo.txt ; then\n"
"  echo \"Found foo.txt\"\n"
"fi"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_shell.xml:913
#, no-c-format
msgid "The test expression can also be abbreviated in angled brackets:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: adm_shell.xml:916
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"if [ -e /tmp/foo.txt ] ; then\n"
"  echo \"Found foo.txt\"\n"
"fi"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_shell.xml:917
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Find more useful expressions at <link xlink:href=\"http://www.cyberciti.biz/"
"nixcraft/linux/docs/uniqlinuxfeatures/lsst/ch03sec02.html\"></link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: adm_shell.xml:924
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating Loops With the <command>for</command> Command"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_shell.xml:925
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>for</command> loop allows you to execute commands to a list of "
"entries. For example, the following code prints some information about PNG "
"files in the current directory:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: adm_shell.xml:930
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"for i in *.png; do\n"
" ls -l $i\n"
"done"
msgstr ""

